briefdescription.para: Tells the frame to show the given menu bar.

parameterdescription.para: The menu bar to associate with the frame.

simplesect.para: If the frame is destroyed, the menu bar and its menus will be destroyed also, so do not delete the menu bar explicitly (except by resetting the frame's menu bar to another frame or NULL). Under Windows, a size event is generated, so be sure to initialize data members properly before calling SetMenuBar(). Note that on some platforms, it is not possible to call this function twice for the same frame object.
